<HEADLINE> S. African President to Arrive in Tanzania On </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki is expected to arrive in Dar es Salaam Sunday for a
two-day working visit to Tanzania, a government statement said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Mbeki who came to power in this May to
visit Tanzania. His visit is in conjunction with the opening
ceremony of the South African Development Community (SADC)
Electoral Commission Forum.
</P>
<P>
Both Tanzania and South Africa are members of the 14-country
SADC regional grouping. The forum will open on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The South African President will be met by his counterpart
Benjamin Mkapa at the Dar es Salaam International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Apart from opening the forum, Mbeki will also hold talks with
his host on issues of mutual interest, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, retired Tanzanian President Ali Hassan Mwinyi will
leave for Beijing Saturday to participate in the celebrations to
mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic
of China scheduled for October 1.
</P>
<P>
Mwinyi will hold discussions with Chinese leaders and officials
of the Shenzhen city government, according to the official
Tanzania Information Services.
</P>
<P>
He will also visit the Great Wall and a dairy farm of superior
breed in the Changping County with his wife Sitti Mwinyi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
