<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Two soldiers of the United Nations Interim Forces in
Lebanon (UNIFIL) were wounded overnight by a roadside bomb in
south Lebanon, the Voice of Lebanon radio reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two soldiers of Fijian contingent inside the UNIFIL were
injured when a bomb exploded under their armored personnel carrier
on the Mansouri-Majdal Zoun road just north of the Israeli
occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
There has been no group claiming responsibility for the blast,
a UNIFIL spokesman said. (BC-Lebanon-UN Soldiers-Wounded)
</P>
