the improvement of the relations between his country and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Cairo for home after a three-day visit, Sudanese
Minister of Health Mahdi Babour Nimir told reporters that although
"disputes still exist" between the two countries, the
Sudanese-Egyptian ties "are improving in a smooth way."
</P>
<P>
The leadership of both countries have underlined the
development of the bilateral ties and officials of the neighbors
are meeting regularly to seek ways of solving the problems, Nimir
said. (BC-Egypt-Sudan-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak called Friday on the
people to join efforts to make overall reforms materialized.
</P>
<P>
In a nationwide televised speech, Mubarak urged the Egyptians
to work together to make sure that the democratic practices are
guaranteed and promoted, freedom of expression entrenched and
concept of social justice will take root. (BC-Egypt-Mubarak)

