<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Students Recover from Food Poisoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 72 Tanzanian
students suffering from food poisoning have recovered and are
attending classes as normal, the government said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The food poisoning took place in the Arusha Technical College
in northern Tanzania on September 20, the official Tanzania
Information Services said in a press release, without giving
reasons of the incident.
</P>
<P>
The statement said two policemen were sent to the college to
investigate the incident. 
