<HEADLINE> Albright to Tour Africa in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will make a 10-day visit to Africa next month,
it was announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The October 17-27 trip, to take her to Guinea, Sierra Leone,
Mali, Nigeria, Kenya and Tanzania, will focus on "ending
conflicts, promoting democracy and supporting economic reform
across the continent," said State Department spokesman James P.
Rubin.
</P>
<P>
The journey is Albright's third to Africa since her assumption
of the post of secretary of state in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Albright is currently in New York attending the general debate
of the 54th Session of the U.N. General Assembly. The two-week
debate runs until October 2. 
</P>
