<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Signs Anti-Terrorism Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Signing the convention, Ethiopian Minister of Justice
Worede-Wold Welde said concerted efforts and cooperation among
states were needed to control the scourge of terrorism in Africa.
</P>
<P>
OAU Assistant Secretary General Daniel Antonio, who signed the
document on behalf of the OAU, said that the support for the
convention was evidenced by the immediate signing of 32 member
states in Algiers.
</P>
<P>
The OAU convention was adopted at the 35th summit of the OAU
assembly of heads of states and government in Algiers this year.
</P>
<P>
It calls for effective system of cooperation among states in
the exchange of information and evidences on terrorists, their
apprehension and prosecution or extraditing them to the countries
where they had committed such crimes. 
</P>
