<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albright to Travel to Africa Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will visit some African countries next month,
the State Department said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The trip to Guinea, Sierra Leone, Mali, Nigeria, Kenya and
Tanzania on October 17-27 will be her third to the continent since
she became secretary of state in 1997.
</P>
<P>
"The visit will focus on America's evolving partnership with
Africa and the common interest we share," spokesman James Rubin
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
In addition to meeting government leaders, Albright plans to
meet with young people, women's organizations and other civil
society groups, Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Africa was seen in Washington as the last market in the world
to be occupied and the United States is expanding its share in
every sector of the continent's economies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
