<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Development Forum to Be Held in Addis Next </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The African Development
Forum '99 is due to be held in Ethiopian capital Addis Ababa from
October 24 to 28, the United Nations Economic Commission for
Africa (ECA) announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ECA-sponsored forum, which meets annually on different
development issues, is an initiative to position an African-driven
development agenda that reflects consensus among major partners
and leads to specific programs for implementation.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's forum is "The Challenge to Africa of
Globalization and the Information Age."
</P>
<P>
Because of the importance of defining African strategies to
engage with the global information economy, this topic has been
chosen for the inaugural African Development Forum, an ECA press
release said.
</P>
<P>
Organizers told reporters that the aim of the forthcoming forum
is to present the key stakeholders in African development with the
results of current research and opinion on key development issues
in order to formulate shared goals and priorities, draft action
programs and define the environment that will enable African
countries to implement these programs.
</P>
<P>
The forum is expected to result in the adoption of country
action plans for the utilization of information and communication
technologies to accelerate social and economic growth, and
recommendations regarding the impact on Africa of globalization
and the information age.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the forum, ECA will organize a post-forum summit
dialog convening selected heads of state and government to ensure
their full support for the country action plans, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
State leaders and government ministers from all African
countries have been invited to attend the five-day meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
