<HEADLINE> Canada Provides Emergency Food Aid for Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Canadian International
Cooperation Minister Maria Minna Friday announced 1 million
Canadian dollars (about 680,000 U.S. dollars) in emergency food
aid to Angola.
</P>
<P>
The minister said "there are some 200 children, women and men
who die every day in Angola because of disease or starvation
related to the war."
</P>
<P>
"The one million Canadian dollars I am announcing today will help
provide food for those most in need," she said.
</P>
<P>
The newly announced assistance brings Canada's contribution to
the south African country to 3.5 million Canadian dollars (about
2.4 million U.S. dollars) this year, according to the official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Up to one million Angolan residents have been displaced since
the resumption of violence in the war-torn country in December
1998. 
</P>
