<HEADLINE> Mubarak Urges Joint Efforts to Promote Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak called Friday on the people to join efforts to make
overall reforms materialized.
</P>
<P>
In a nationwide televised speech, Mubarak urged the Egyptians
to work together to make sure that the democratic practices are
guaranteed and promoted, freedom of expression entrenched and
concept of social justice will take root.
</P>
<P>
Ever since the Egyptian people entrusted him with the
leadership responsibility in October 1981, he and the Egyptian
people have pledged to undertake the duties for national
development, the Egyptian president said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who was re-elected in 1987 and 1993, delivered the
speech ahead of the referendum due on Sunday to endorse parliament
nomination for him to be in power for another six years.
</P>
<P>
He called on the 20 million tangible voters to participate in
the referendum, which he said "is not on the choice of a person
but on a program of overall revival of Egypt."
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian people should concentrate their efforts on
realizing the goal of developing the nation, Mubarak said.
</P>
<P>
After the economic reforms that was kicked off in 1991 have
achieved the targeted goals, Egypt should move towards social and
cultural development in a bid to make tangible progress in the
people's overall living standard, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We, standing on the threshold of the 21st century, must take
the necessary steps for a comprehensive national program aimed at
realizing a strong technological advancement, providing free and
democratic climate and strengthening the role of governmental and
non-governmental institutions," Mubarak said. 
</P>
