<HEADLINE> Bank Of Scotland Bids For Natwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 24 (Xinhua) - The Bank of Scotland launched a
surprise 20.85 billion pounds bid Friday for NatWest in what would
be the biggest takeover in the history of British banking.
</P>
<P>
The proposed deal would create the UK's biggest banking group
by value after HSBC and LloydsTSB, overtaking Barclays which is
currently the third largest.
</P>
<P>
Under the Bank of Scotland proposal, NatWest shareholders would
end up holding approximately 68 percent of the total issued Bank
of Scotland shares.
</P>
<P>
NatWest has a market capitalisation of 17.7 billion pounds,
more than twice as big as Bank of Scotland's 8.9 billion, based on
Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Scotland's offer would be conditional on NatWest's
proposed 10.7 billion pounds takeover of insurance group Legal and
General Plc not proceeding.
</P>
<P>
However, the Bank of Scotland said NatWest would remain a
separate unit, retaining its name. 
</P>
</TEXT>
