<HEADLINE> National Exam for Asset Valuers Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The national examination for
the qualification of certified asset valuers in China was held
today, with more than 60,000 applicants taking the test.
</P>
<P>
A Ministry of Finance official said that the number of
applicants this year greatly increased and five categories,
instead of the previous four, were tested.
</P>
<P>
He said the validity of the examination results will be
extended to two years.
</P>
<P>
The exam, co-organized by the Ministry of Finance and the
Ministry of Personnel, is the third of its kind since the system
of asset valuers was established.
</P>
<P>
The official expected that the results of the exam will be
announced in December. 
</P>
