<HEADLINE> ABC All-star Game to be Held in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Newly-crowned Asian champion
China is to face the challenges from an allied army of top
hoopsters from 10 countries and regions when the third Asian
Basketball Council All-Star Games is held in Guangzhou, China, on
October 6.
</P>
<P>
According to the press conference here on Friday, the Asian
championship MVP winner Hu Weidong is to spearhead the host
Chinese national team, who captured the 20th Asian men's
championship title in Fukuoka, Japan just a couple of weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Olympics-bound Chinese national team will take on
the all-star team led by sharp shooters Hur Jae of South Korea and
power forward Michael Takahashi of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The 14-member Asian All-Star team also include hoop stars from
Chinese Taipei, Lebanon, Hong Kong of China, Saudi Arabia, Syria,
the Philippines, Kuwait and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou game is the third edition of its kind. In the
First Asian All-Star Game held in South Korea in 1997, the hosts
beat the Asian All-Star team 123-97.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the second game was held in Chinese Taipei while the
host team won by downing the Asian allied side 115-97. 
