<HEADLINE> Bus Crash Kills 14 in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were
killed in a bus crash Friday night near Kokstad in the southeast
region of KwaZulu- Natal, South Africa, according to a local
police report.
</P>
<P>
About 25 to 30 people were injured when the Surens Coastal
Express passenger bus crashed into a tree in thick mist on a
straight stretch of road about four kilometers outside Kokstad,
said Police inspector Quinton Heslop.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by South African Press Association as saying that
 the bus, while traveling on the N2 highway from Durban to
Matatiele, had a portion of it ripped off in the midnight
collision.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth bus crash since Wednesday. The previous
three bus accidents occurred in the country had killed a total of
53 people.
</P>
<P>
The Saturday Star reported that Transport Minister Dullah Omar
was to meet a number of bus company representatives to discuss the
recent spate of fatal bus accidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
