<HEADLINE> Power Plant Completed Ahead of Schedule in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A thermal power plant with a
generating capacity of 1.2 million kw was completed today 20
months ahead of schedule in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the plant, which started in October, 1996, is
the fastest in China thanks to the application of new techniques,
which also saved 500 million yuan in cost.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.4 billion yuan (774 million U.S.dollars) of funds
have been poured into the construction.  
</P>
