<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Opens Foreign Economic, Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SUZHOU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A four-day foreign economic and
trade fair opened today in Suzhou city of east China's Jiangsu
province, attracting over 1,500 foreign businessmen from Asia,
Europe, America and Oceania, and 90 domestic large-scale firms and
listed companies.
</P>
<P>
The fair, with 190 booths and held in the newly-built Suzhou
International Conference and Exhibition Center, covers a large
variety of trade categories, including textiles, electricity,
metallurgy, chemistry, machinery and medicine.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou, one of China's most developed cities, reported an
export volume of 2.85 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of
1999, up 25.4 percent from the year-ago period, while the whole
country's exports have declined.
</P>
<P>
The city has so far had 7,043 foreign-funded firms and
introduced a total of 30.1 billion U.S. dollars in foreign funds,
ranking third in China following Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The city also held a three-day technical exchange fair today.
</P>
</TEXT>
