<HEADLINE> China's Coal Mines Urged to Pay Pension Insurance for Retirees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice-premier Wu
Bangguo has urged the country's coal mines to pay pension
insurance for their retirees and the arrears in their wages.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in Beijing today at a national conference on pension
insurance for coal mines, the vice-premier said the matter is of
utmost importance to social stability.
</P>
<P>
He announced that the pension arrears of major state-owned coal
mines would be paid from the state coffer after going through
necessary auditing by authorities.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged banks to help coal mines recover their debts, which
have been partly responsible for the mines' cash shortages.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also called on state-owned coal mines to step
up reform with the aim of establishing a modern enterprise system,
including the streamlining of redundant staff to increase
efficiency and profits. 
</P>
