<HEADLINE> Gold Prices Rise Sharply in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices shot up by 80
rupees (1.86 U.S. dollars) Saturday on the bullion market in
Mumbai (Bombay) on firm overseas advices.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and 22-carat gold rose by 80 rupees (1.86 U.S.
dollars) and 70 rupees (1.63 U.S. dollars) and closed at 4,230
rupees (98.37 U.S. dollars) per ten gram and 3,910 rupees (90.93
U.S. dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, ready silver (.999 fineness) dropped by 10 rupees
(0.23 U.S. dollar) to close at 8115 rupees (188.72 U.S. dollars)
per kilogram from the previous close of 8125 rupees (188.95 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) improved to 7,995 rupees (185.93
U.S. dollars) per kg. from 7,975 rupees (185.47 U.S. dollars).
</P>
