<HEADLINE> China National Invention Exhibition Reports Brisk Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China's 12th National
Invention Exhibition has recorded a historic 2.1 billion yuan
turnover in technological trade, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 621 inventions were sold at the exhibition, which
closed recently in Ningbo city, Zhejiang Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 inventions in the fields of machinery,
electronics, biology, medicine, chemicals, energy conservation and
environmental conservation technology were on display.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and four inventions won golden medals at the show,
while 156 won silver medals and 221 bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 businessmen visited the exhibition.
Multinational companies such as Motorola and Philips were
reportedly among the potential buyers.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers, a total of 10,343 inventions were
exhibited at the 11 prior events, 15 percent of which have been
turned into products.  
</P>
