<HEADLINE> 10 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of Turkey's
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in recent
military operations in southeastern Turkey, an official statement
said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that Turkish security forces had wiped out one PKK
militant in Kozluk town of Batman province, five in Hani town of
Diyarbakir province, three in Sirnak province, and one in Tunceli
province.
</P>
<P>
The security forces captured one PKK rebel in Tunceli
province, said the statement, adding that two PKK guerrillas
surrendered to the security forces in the region.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. Over 37,000 people have
been killed in conflicts between the PKK and the government
troops since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
