planned protest rally against the government of Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the major opposition party, Pakistan People's
Party, said that about 3,500 of its workers including members of
parliament have been rounded up in a massive sweep by the police
in Karachi.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, hundreds of activists of the ethnic Motahidda Qaumi
Movement (MQM) have also been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Karachi is the stronghold of MQM which represents Urdu-speaking
immigrants from India.
</P>
<P>
Police launched crackdown overnight against leaders of the
newly-formed 19-party Grand Democratic Alliance, an
anti-government coalition, following a two-month ban on rallies in
the southern port city.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said that police have blockaded all roads leading to
the venue of the planned rally in the center of Karachi.
</P>
<P>
MQM had been a coalition partner of the ruling Pakistan Muslim
League in southern Sindh province until last year when Prime
Minister Sharif dismissed the provincial government and imposed
direct federal rule after accusing MQM of involvement in terrorist
activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
