<HEADLINE> ADB Funds Major Power Plant in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a 3.5
billion yuan power plant has started in Yuzhou city, Henan
Province in central China.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the Yuzhou Power Plant will have two
generating units, each with a capacity of 350,000 kw, and will be
operational in the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
The power plant, a major national project for the ninth five-
year plan (1996-2000), is being built with a 210 million U.S.
dollar loan from the Asia Development Bank (ADB).
</P>
<P>
The Xuchang Longgang Electricity Generating Co., Ltd. is
responsible for the construction and management of the plant.
</P>
<P>
Westinghouse Corp. and Bailey Controls, both U.S. companies,
and ABB of Australia will supply the major equipment for the plant.
</P>
