<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Southern Iran, Houses Slightly Damaged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.1
degrees on Richter scale hit Iran's southern coastal province of
Bushehr Friday night, causing slight damage to a number of rural
houses.
</P>
<P>
The seismography base of Shiraz, affiliated to the Geophysics
Institute of Tehran University, registered the epicenter of the
tremor 160 kilometers southwest of Shiraz, capital city of
Bushehr's neighboring Fars province.
</P>
<P>
The tremor hit the area at 10:47 p.m. local time (1917 GMT)
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Reports on Saturday said that the quake inflicted minor damage
to several rural houses in a number of villages. But so far, no
reports on casualties are available. 
