<HEADLINE> Fuzhou-Quanzhou Expressway Opens to traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A 154-km-long expressway opens
to traffic today, connecting two coastal cities of Fuzhou and
Quanzhou in east China's Fujian province.
</P>
<P>
The expressway, built from 1997, involves a total investment of
4.67 billion yuan with two two-way lanes, three tunnels and 13
bridges. The speed limit for the expressway is 120 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will further improve the transportation and
investment environment for the eastern province, authorities noted.
</P>
<P>
Fujian province began the expressway construction in 1994. So
far, the length of expressways in Fujian has reached 280 km,
linking five booming cities along southeastern coast in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has designed an expressway network of more than 1,200 km
across the province and another 700-km expressway is expected to
open traffic by 2002.  
</P>
