<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Blood Bank" Set Up In Case of Need for Air Accident Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 100 staffers at Tianhe
Airport of Wuhan, the capital of central China's Hubei province,
have signed contracts on donating blood in case of need for
victims at any possible air accident.
</P>
<P>
The voluntary program, the first of its kind launched in the
country, was organized by the first-aid center of the airport,
based on the idea that victims suffering from blood loss in any
air accident will face danger due to the failure of blood supply
caused by the long distance between blood bank and venue.
</P>
<P>
The airport is often quite distant from the urban area. An
official from the station said that 90 percent of air disasters
occur near the airport within 10 minutes after an aircraft takes
off or lands.
</P>
<P>
The contracts also ensure that once needed, the volunteers can
go somewhere in the city to donate bloods to accident victims.
</P>
</TEXT>
