<HEADLINE> Spain Sweep New Zealand in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Spain routed New Zealand 3-
0 in a Davis Cup 2000 group relegation playoff, after a solid
straight sets win by its doubles players in Hamilton, New Zealand
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 7-6, 7-6, 6-4 victory gives Spain an assured world group
place in next year's Davis Cup, where they will join another seven
nations.
</P>
<P>
Julian Alonso and Juan Balcells rocked the Hamilton crowd in
the indoor Mystery Creek stadium.
</P>
<P>
The doubles win put the tie beyond doubt and followed a smooth
win in Friday's second singles by Francisco Clavet over New
Zealand's best rated player, Steven.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's defeat also ended an unbeaten Davis Cup doubles run
for Greenhalgh and Steven who have won in the past over China and
Korea.
</P>
<P>
Spanish captain Manolo Santana whose worst moment came in the
second set of the opening singles game on Friday when his top
player Felix Mantilla, world ranked 18th, needed treatment for a
trapped nerve in his back.
</P>
<P>
Mantilla played on but lost the next two sets, and nearly let
the game slip away to his 21-year-old opponent Mark Nielsen,
before rallying to win through in five sets.
</P>
<P>
Clavet helped restore the side's confidence overnight by
beating Steven with apparent ease, 6-2, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Two more reverse singles are scheduled for Sunday but the
results will be academic. 
</P>
