<HEADLINE> Ugandan Cattle Farmers Urged to Minimize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has urged cattle farmers to minimize the cost of
production through cost- effective farming.
</P>
<P>
The president made the appeal while launching the country's
Beef Producers Association at the Uganda Manufacturers Association
show grounds here Friday, a press release from the President's
Office said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At the function, the president announced the lifting of the ban
on the importation of semen, stressing that breeding experts
should work hard to develop local capacity in semen production.
</P>
<P>
Farmers should be encouraged to have their cattle vaccinated to
reduce incidence of cattle mortality and de-worm cows at least
twice a year, he said, adding that the provision of mineral salts
is crucial for successful ranching in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said private entrepreneurs are encouraged to do beef
processing and marketing and the government is ready to co-invest
with them to help solve the problem of financing.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the Beef Producers Association is hailed as a
good move because it could help make important follow-up
procedures on issues crucial for the development of the beef
industry in the country.  
</P>
