<HEADLINE> 31st AEM to Be Held in Singapore Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The 31st ASEAN Economic
Ministers Meeting (AEM) and a series of related meetings will be
held here from September 27 to October 2, the Singaporean Ministry
of Trade and Industry (MTI) announced in a press release Saturday.
</P>
<P>
MTI said Singapore Minister for Trade and Industry George Yeo
will chair the AEM and the other meetings in conjunction with the
31st AEM include the second ASEAN Investment Area (AIA) Council
meeting and the 13th ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) Council meeting.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) economic
ministers will also have consultations with their counterparts
from CER (the Australia and New Zealand Closer Economic Relations)
countries and Japan and members of the ASEAN Chamber of Commerce
and Industry, MTI said.
</P>
<P>
According to MTI, the ministers are expected to discuss the
deepening of member countries' commitment to the Common Effective
Preferential Tariff (CEPT) Scheme for the AFTA such as the
reduction of tariffs to zero percent and accelerating the transfer
of products which are currently not included in the tariff
reduction schedule into the CEPT Scheme.
</P>
<P>
Also on agenda are discussions on the implementation of the
Framework Agreement on the ASEAN Investment Area as well as the
expansion of its coverage, and the organization of the Joint ASEAN
Investment Roadshows proposed by Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong.
</P>
<P>
In the consultations with their counterparts, the ASEAN
ministers will explore ways to enhance economic cooperation with
CER countries and Japan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, a Protocol on the Special Arrangement for
Sensitive and Highly Sensitive Products and an agreement on
Extension of the Memorandum of Understanding on Cooperation in
Standards and Conformance between ASEAN and the CER countries to
Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar will also be signed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
