<HEADLINE> Sixty Percent of China's Businesspeople Use Internet: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Sixty percent of the
businesspeople in China are using the Internet, according to a
recent survey conducted by the Chinese edition of Fortune Magazine.
</P>
<P>
About 95 percent of those people in China who haven't yet used
the Internet plan to do so.
</P>
<P>
Among the 60 percent of the businesspeople currently using the
Internet, 56 percent log-on at their offices, 43 percent go online
at home, and 21 percent do so at both places.
</P>
<P>
Ninetysix percent of those polled cited the Internet as a
useful source of business information.
</P>
<P>
Sixtyone percent said that the companies they work for have
homepages, among which industries sectors including transportation,
law, tourism and hotels contribute are the majority. Nearly 50
percent of the state-owned enterprises have homepages, while most,
about 56 percent, of private and collective companies do not.
</P>
<P>
Ninetythree percent believe that the Internet will play an
vital role in their business development in the future. 
</P>
