<DOCNO> XIE19990925.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vandenbroucke Wins 19th Stage of Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Frank Vandenbroucke
won Friday's 19th stage of the 21-leg Tour of Spain cycling while
German Jan Ullrich continued his 31-second overall lead heading
into the final two days.
</P>
<P>
Vandenbroucke clocked Friday's 185-kilometer from El Escorial
to Avila in west-central Spain in 4 hours 54 minutes and 18
seconds, beating Spaniard Mikel Zarrabeitia by 13 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Heras of Spain and Russian Pavel Tonkov led a group a
group of six that were another seven seconds back.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich finished 20 seconds behind Vandenbroucke, in sixth
place and just ahead of his nearest rival, Igor Gonzalez Galdeano
of Spain.
</P>
<P>
The Tour ends Sunday in central Madrid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
