<HEADLINE> Weekly Diplomatic News Highlights (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Peng on September 21 told Fred Gollop, president of the
Senate of Barbados, that China values its ties with Barbados and
would like to pursue long-term Sino-Barbadian friendly and
cooperative ties in accordance with the Five Principles of
Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his satisfaction with the smooth growth of
bilateral ties since the two countries forged diplomatic relations,
saying that they have conducted cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his hope that cooperation between the parliaments
of the two countries will spur the advancement of bilateral ties
as a whole.
</P>
<P>
 China to Host Asia-Pacific Cooperative Ministers'
Conference
</P>
<P>
 China will host the Fifth Asia-Pacific Cooperative Ministers'
Conference (APCMC) during October 11-16 this year in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The conference, hosted by the Chinese Government and the All-
China Federation of Supply &AMP; Marketing Cooperatives (ACFSMC), will
be the first of its kind ever held in China.
</P>
<P>
Li Chunsheng, secretary general of the ACFSMC, said on
September 21 at a news conference that government officials from
28 countries of the Asia-Pacific Region, Africa, and Europe will
take part in the gathering, and the total number of participants
is estimated at some 200, he said.
</P>
<P>
Senior CPC Official Meets Nepalese Communist Party Leader
</P>
<P>
A senior Communist Party of China (CPC) official said here on
Tuesday that the CPC is ready to strengthen its friendly relations
of cooperation with the Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxist
Leninist, CPN-UML).
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, told CPN-UML
General Secretary Madhav Kumar Nepal that the CPC is willing to
enhance the relationship under the principles of maintaining
independence with the initiative in one's own hands, total
equality, mutual respect, and non-interference in each other's
internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
 NPC Vice-Chairwoman Meets Guatemalan Visitors
</P>
<P>
He Luli, vice-chairwoman of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here on September 21 with a
parliamentary delegation of Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
Spokeswoman: China Attaches Importance to Fortune Forum
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin will announce the opening of the Fortune
global forum to be held in Shanghai and make a keynote speech in
the opening session, said Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman
Zhang Qiyue here on September 21.
</P>
<P>
Zhang told the regular press conference that Chinese Premier
Zhu Rongji is scheduled to meet some of the participants in the
forum later in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets Antigua and Barbuda Governor-
General
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin met with James Carlisle, governor-
general of Antigua and Barbuda, here on September 22, praising the
smooth development of ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted out that China and Antigua and Barbuda, both
developing countries, have had similar historic experience and
also faced the common task of developing national economy,
improving people's life and safeguarding world peace.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is willing to make concerted efforts
with the government of Antigua and Barbuda in a bid to bring a
long-term, stable and sustainable bilateral ties well into the
coming century in line with the principles of equality, mutual
support, increasing contacts and friendship, and expanding
cooperation," Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
