<HEADLINE> Weekly Diplomatic News Highlights (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The visitors are here for the two-month-long 3rd China-Africa
Seminar for Economic and Management Officials, which began in
August. The 20 participants from 12 African countries have been to
various coastal and inland provinces and cities.
</P>
<P>
 Jiang Zemin Meets CITIC International Advisory Members
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin said here Friday during a meeting with
six well-known international businessmen that China will do its
utmost to restructure the State-owned enterprises (SOEs) so as to
guarantee a sustainable, rapid and healthy growth of the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
He explained the major policies covering the reform and
development of SOEs, adopted at the just-concluded 4th plenary
session of the 15th CPC Central Committee, to Maurice Greenberg,
chairman of AIG of the United States, and five other members of
the International Advisory Council of the China International
Trust and Investment Corp. (CITIC), who are in China to attend a
CITIC meeting.
</P>
<P>
 China's Top Legislator Meets Singaporean Guests
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, told visiting Singaporean Senior Minister Lee
Kuan Yew that the frequent visits between Chinese and Singaporean
ranking officials indicate the close bilateral relationship.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks in his meeting with Lee here Friday at the
Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Li said he was delighted to meet Lee, an old friend of China,
again on the Mid-autumn Festival today. He spoke highly of the
active efforts made by Lee to promote the growth of bilateral ties
and wished Lee's current visit a complete success.
</P>
<P>
 Vice-President Meets Malta Guests
</P>
<P>
Vice-president Hu Jintao, in a meeting with a Malta Labor Party
delegation here this afternoon, said the people of China and Malta
enjoy a traditional friendship and that bilateral relations have
had constant development since diplomatic ties were established 27
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Maltese cooperation in politics, economy, culture, and
other fields has been effective and bilateral relations have
served as a model of relations between countries with different
social systems, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier On China's 50-Year Diplomacy
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, in a recent interview with the China
Radio International, has said the independent foreign policy of
peace has been China's diplomatic guideline in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
He recalled China's diplomatic work, and concluded that as long
as China adhere to the central task of economic development,
continue its reform and opening up, and follow the diplomatic
guideline, it will become prosperous and its diplomatic work will
be more fruitful.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister: PLA Foreign Exchange Achievements "
Notable"
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian said here Friday that high-
level foreign exchanges conducted by officers of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) have scored "notable" achievements
since the People's Republic of China was founded 50 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
a state councilor, made the statement during an interview with
Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
Chi noted that the PLA exchange with foreign militaries "was
established by the elder proletarian revolutionaries" and has "
grown steadily thanks to the care of the three generations of the
CPC leadership." 
</P>
</TEXT>
