<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Wushu Championships Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian '99 National Wushu
Championships was opened by the National Sports Council (KONI)
Chairman Wismoyo Arismunandar here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The event, scheduled to be staged until September 27, will not
only serve as the National Sports Championships (PON) qualifying
round but also for the world wushu event to be held in Hong Kong,
China, from November 1-7.
</P>
<P>
Joined by a total of 325 participants from 16 provincial
federations, the showcases feature two categories: Taolo and
Sanshow.
</P>
<P>
Taolo, similar to Kata in karate, is divided into five
classifications -- Tai Chi Quan, Nan Quan, Cang Quan, Short Weapon
and Long Weapon -- while Sanshow (karate's Kumite) comprises seven
competitions ranging from 48 kg to 75 kg.
</P>
<P>
In its effort to introduce the sports to the community, the
event was also marked by a performance of Barongsai, a Chinese-
originated traditional dance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
