<HEADLINE> 4th Phase of Lok Sabha Polling Begins in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The fourth phase of polling
for the 13th Lok Sabha elections began Saturday morning in 74
constituencies in nine states across the country amidst tight
security.
</P>
<P>
some 83 million voters will decide the electoral fortunes of
695 lok Sabha candidates.
</P>
<P>
Security measures have been tightened in view of violence in
the third phase of voting, which claimed 47 poll-related deaths.
In Bihar state alone, 38 people were killed.
</P>
<P>
Latest exit polls conducted by Indian media has given the
BJP-led National Democratic alliance (NDA) a clear edge over the
Congress after the first three phases of polling.
</P>
<P>
However, political analysts said that the gap between the NDA
and the Congress will be narrowed in the fourth phase of voting.
</P>
</TEXT>
