<DOCNO> XIE19990925.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Play Greater Role in World: Cyprus' Top Lawmaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The fast-growing China market
is helping the country to play an important role in the post-Cold
War world's new political and economic order, Spyros Kyprianou,
president of the house of representatives of Cyprus, said.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, Kyprianou said the People's
Republic of China has gained great achievements in various fields
since its founding 50 years ago, which attracted worldwide
attention.
</P>
<P>
Kyprianou, once president and foreign minister of Cyprus, said
that he has been following with interest the development in China.
During the U.N. General Assembly in 1971, Kyprianou, who was then
Cyprus' foreign minister, signed the agreement to establish
diplomatic relations with China. He visited China in 1984 as
president of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Kyprianou said China's political, economic, social and cultural
realities could not be experienced and judged better by anyone
else than its own people. China's ambitious economic reform
program launched in 1978 is certainly of great inspiration, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that late senior Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's broad
vision of a giant state closer and more accessible to the world
and the policy that he introduced and is followed by his
successors not only benefited the country itself, but also
prepared China to meet the post-Cold War challenges with an
unparalleled stable growth averaging 7 to 10 percent since 1990.
</P>
<P>
He said the increasingly important role China is called upon to
play in the world and the regional economy, the country's
performance with regard to financial issues as well as its
potential to become a leading figure even under the most
unfavorable conditions have added to the country's promising
profile of an emerging economic power in modern times.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the recent visit to China by Cyprus' President
Glafcos Clerides, Kyprianou stressed the excellent relations which
"have always existed between Cyprus and China," and have since
gained a new impetus.
</P>
<P>
As parliament speaker, Kyprianou pointed out that at the
parliamentary level, the two countries have consolidated
harmonious relations and cooperation over the year through regular
exchange of visits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
