<HEADLINE> Amazing Achievements Made in Reconstruction: Serb Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The reconstruction of the
Serbia Republic of Yugoslavia has made "amazing achievements,"
Serb officials said at a news briefing here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dragomir Tomich, deputy prime minister of the Serb government
told reporters that most of the factories damaged during NATO
bombings have resumed operation, and 75,000 workers have returned
their posts.
</P>
<P>
All the achievements were made through self-reliance, Tomich
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the current situation, the economic growth rate is
expected to attain the target of 15 percent in the second half of
this year, he added.
</P>
<P>
The financial reconstruction has been finished, and before
winter comes, all the damaged civilian houses would be fully
repaired, Tomich said.
</P>
<P>
Serb Agricultural Minister Jovan Babovich said the agricultural
harvest this year will not only be able to ensure the supply of
daily necessities for all residents but also the needs of
strategic reserves and exports.
</P>
<P>
The total output of major farm products of Serbia will reach 22
billion dinars (about 1.94 billion U.S. dollars), an increase of 4
billion dinars (354 million dollars) compared to last year, the
minister said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
