<HEADLINE> Taxis Ready for Fortune Forum in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- About 1,500 cars from the
Friendship State Guest Cars, Dazhong and Qiangsheng taxi companies
in Shanghai City are getting ready for the upcoming Fortune Global
Forum to be held China's biggest business hub.
</P>
<P>
The three companies have also bought 310 new Buick and Benz
cars and acquired Nissans, Fords, Cadillacs and Audis at a cost of
more than 200 million yuan (24.15 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"We chose 706 drivers who have at least four years of driving
experience and no accident record," said Shen Zhengdong, a senior
officer with the Shanghai Friendship Taxi Service.
</P>
<P>
Every driver has been trained in various fields such as English,
protocol and traveling routes.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that these drivers and the cars chosen not only
expresses the importance of quality service in the city but also
publicizes Shanghai's taxis throughout the would.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai now has more than 400 taxi companies, seven of which
boast nearly 2,000 taxis each. And almost 8,800 taxis in Shanghai
now use liquefied petrol gas.  
</P>
