<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian Currency Devaluation Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ecuadorian exchange market
continued boiling Friday when the U.S. dollar parity surpassed the
15,000 sucre barrier.
</P>
<P>
The dollar quotation closed Friday at 13,050 sucres for
purchase and 15,300 sucres for sale in the Banco de Pichincha, one
of the biggest bourses of this country, going to an average of 14,
175 sucres, which meant a 1.6 percent increase over the 13,945
sucres Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The dollar quotation on Thursday was 13,800 sucres for buying
and 14,090 for sale.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of Ecuador (BCE) blamed on speculative factors
the heavy pressures on the rate of exchange for the last days.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Friday, the BCE pointed out that
speculative pressures distort the prospects of macroeconomic order
the country is striving for, especially the reduction of inflation.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador is facing its worst economic slump. The government is
working on a plan to restructure the debts in an effort to reduce
its total debt burden of 16 billion dollars, representing 110
percent of its gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
