<HEADLINE> Panama Destroys Marihuana Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian antidrug
authorities destroyed 14 hectares of marihuana and opium poppy
plants cultivated in the Isla del Rey region of the country.
</P>
<P>
The destruction of the plants was part of the "Lagarto"
operation started more than one month ago in the Pacific littoral,
National Air Service (SAN) director Ruben Dario Arguelles said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The operation was performed by antidrug authorities and the
National Air and Maritime Services.
</P>
<P>
The marihuana and opium poppy plants were camouflaged among
rice and other crops.
</P>
<P>
The authorities do not know who are the owners of the land
where the crops were found, National Maritime Service director
Jorge Isaza said.
</P>
<P>
Antidrug authorities seized drugs and arrested people with
weapons and cash in their hands during the operation, and also
found one dozen undocumented Colombians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
