<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Resumes Relations With British Credit Agency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Cuba (BCC)
announced Friday the resumption of relations with the British
Export Credits Guarantee Department (ECGB), which were interrupted
more than a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
Both institutions signed in London a document that "opens the
way" for the British agency to offer fresh credits to Cuba that
will encourage the export of British capital goods to the island,
said the ECGB in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The ECGB, which is answerable to the Secretary of State for
Commerce and Industry, grants credits for the foreign acquisition
of goods or services from Great Britain.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, Cuba will reimburse the ECGB short
term debts for 8.5 million sterling pounds (14 million U.S.
dollars) in exchange for new credits for the same amount.
</P>
<P>
The ECGB condoned Cuban delays in the payment of interests on
overdue debts, said the Central Bank of Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
