<DOCNO> XIE19990925.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Businessmen Urge End to Brazil-Argentina Trade Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A Brazilian businessmen
organization has demanded the end of a trade dispute between
Brazil and Argentina, which it says weakens the Southern Common
Market (Mercosur) in its negotiations with other blocs.
</P>
<P>
"We are spending energy internally that should be directed to
combat protectionism abroad," Sao Paulo State Industrial
Federation Foreign Trade (FIESP) director Luiz Fernando Furlan was
quoted as saying by the local press on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil and Argentina recently raised barriers to their
reciprocal exports. The two countries are the biggest trade
partners of Mercosur, the largest regional trade bloc in South
America which also includes Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The protectionist measures mutually applied by the two Mercosur
partners are detrimental to the bloc, since they weaken it in its
strategic negotiations, Furlan said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, FIESP president Horacio Lafer also asked to end the
controversy because of the pending Mercosur-European Union
negotiations and the creation of the Free Trade Area of the
Americas (FTAA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
