<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two German Jets Collide in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Two German air force
aircraft collided Friday during training over southeastern New
Mexico State of the United States, but the four pilots ejected
safely and parachuted to the ground, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted Holloman Air Force Base as saying that the
pilots were taken to a hospital in Carlsbad.
</P>
<P>
The accident, involving two European-made Tornado aircraft
belonging to the German air force, happened shortly before 3 p.m.
local time.
</P>
<P>
Germany has trained its pilots at Holloman for years, and its
Flying Training Center there currently has some 580 military
personnel and about 25 Tornado airplanes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
