<HEADLINE> 82 Cars Participate in 27th Cyprus Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 82 cars, 11
foreign and 71 Cypriot crews, Friday started this year's 1,050km
Cyprus Rally.
</P>
<P>
The three-day contest has 17 special stages and is likely to
show the winner of this year's European Championship.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, the first let of the rally includes
two special stages, covering a distance of 30 kilometers and is
expected to finish Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The second leg begins early Saturday morning from Nicosia,
includes nine special stages and drivers will cover a total
distance of 544 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's final leg includes six stages and will cover 476
kilometers. It is scheduled to finish at Nicosia's Eleftheria
Square at 5:30 pm.
</P>
<P>
The largest foreign participation is the Greek one with six
crews, four of which are fighting for the National Cup of A/5
category.
</P>
<P>
The start of the Rally was given by Cyprus' Education and
Culture Minister Ouranios Ioannides and Undersecretary to the
President Pantelis Kouros. 
