<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Basket Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan oil basket
price increased by an average of 29 U.S. cents to 20.69 U.S.
dollars per barrel this week, the Mines and energy Ministry (MEM)
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
Due to recovery of crude demand in the international market,
the average value of the Venezuelan oil basket has risen to 13.95
dollars per barrel, compared with the average price of 10.57
dollars in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela is the largest oil producer and exporter in the
Western hemisphere. Oil represents 70 percent of Venezuela's
exports and over 50 percent of the national revenue. 
